CARMEN XVI.

To Pompeius Grosphus, of whom nothing is known but that in Epp. i. 12 Horace recommends him to Iccius, then acting as agent sor Agrippa in Sicily, where Grosphus had property, as the ode states.

l. 1. Otium: note the emphatic repetitions in 11. 5. 6. The word covers more than either ‘ peace,‘ or ‘ repose‚' in English, having something of both ideas. ⁴

bello furiosa Thrace: a general epithet. Virg. Aen. iii. 13 calls it Alavortia terra.
